## 2. Run ALL existing tests

After writing integration tests, verify ALL tests still pass:
- `cd backend && python -m pytest tests/ -v`
- `cd mobile && npx tsc --noEmit && npx jest --passWithNoTests`
- `cd dashboard && npx tsc --noEmit && npm run build`

Fix any regressions if found.

## 3. README.md

Create a comprehensive README at the project root:

```markdown
# Yuni

Group dating app for university students. Get matched into a group of 4-6,
go on a group date, connect with whoever you vibe with.

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.12+
- Node.js 18+
- Docker (for PostgreSQL)

### Setup

1. Start the database:
   docker compose up -d

2. Backend:
   cd backend
   python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   alembic upgrade head
   python -m app.seed  # seed demo data
   uvicorn app.main:app --reload

3. Admin Dashboard:
   cd dashboard
   npm install
   npm run dev
   # Open http://localhost:3000
   # Login: admin@mail.utoronto.ca / admin123

4. Mobile App:
   cd mobile
   npm install
   npx expo start
   # Scan QR code with Expo Go

### API Documentation
Backend API docs: http://localhost:8000/docs

### Running Tests
# Backend
cd backend && python -m pytest tests/ -v

# Mobile
cd mobile && npx tsc --noEmit && npx jest

# Dashboard
cd dashboard && npx tsc --noEmit && npm run build

### Tech Stack
- Backend: Python, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, PostgreSQL
- Mobile: React Native (Expo), TypeScript
- Dashboard: Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Real-time: WebSockets

### Project Structure
[Include the directory tree from CLAUDE.md]
```

